: The pongala offering at the Varanad Devi temple at Cherthala will be held on January 18, coinciding with the Makara Bharani festival. The programme will start at 8.30 a.m.Tantri Kadiakkolmana Krishnan Nampoothiry will light the hearth for the pongala on the temple premises at 8.30 a.m. Distribution of pongala coupons has begun, said Varanadu Devaswom representatives.The Makara pongala at the Malayalappuzha Devi temple will be held on January 15. Minister for Home Ramesh Chennithala will inaugurate the programme at 8.30 a.m.Facilities will be made for devotees to offer pongala along the roads leading to the temple, the Malayalappuzha Devaswom authorities said. â€” Special Correspondent